editorialSummary.text: Colorful ice cream parlor chain known for its many flavors plus sorbet & yogurt.

originalText.text: Every time I go to buy Ice cream  there’s a big tall Lurch holding my order hostage until I pay, if you don’t trust people then get out of the neighborhood and take that tall Monster with you.

originalText.text: The place was really neat and the customer service was great. There were so many flavors of ice cream and everything was still fresh. It was a pretty cold day today but it was very worth it.

originalText.text: Worlds smallest scoop for 4.35. Not worth it. Especially when workers are seemingly talking about you in their native language.

originalText.text: It is both a dunkin donuts and baskin robbins and I love that. It is always being cleaned and I love going between 11pm-4am because I'm a night person and the employees there at that time are literally the best and sweetest. I do feel they need an armed guard or policeman during night hours because it is 24/7 and it can be dangerous for only 2 employees at night. But other than that best costumer service ever and the wait is super quick. They keep me and I notice other people as regular customers. They make you feel like friends not just customers to get in and out and that is how any store should be.
